==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: manta ray
<hw>manta ray</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An extremely large pelagic
tropical ray of the family <fam>Mobulidae</fam>, that feeds on plankton
and small fishes. It is usually harmless but its size (up to 20 feet
across and up to a ton in weight) make it dangerous if harpooned. Called
also <altname>manta</altname>, <altname>sea devil</altname> and
<altname>devilfish</altname>. See also <er>Cephaloptera</er> and <er>Sea
devil</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mantchoo</ent>⟦br⟧
